Ukrainian President  Viktor Yanukovych  fired Environment Minister Mykola Zlochevskyi.  Zlochevskyi was replaced by Eduard Stavytskyi, formerly the
chairman of the State Geology and Natural Resources Service,
Yanukovych said in a decree published on his website today.
Zlochevskyi was appointed deputy head of the National Security
and Defense Council.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Moscow at 
